The paper discusses the problem of genome data privacy and its implications for computer science, medicine, and public policy. It reviews the state-of-the-art regarding privacy attacks on genomic data and strategies for mitigating such attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the challenges for genome data privacy and presents a framework to systematize the analysis of threats and the design of countermeasures, which could be relevant to the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
